title: Jungle Girl (Movie Serial - 1941)
description:
A 1941 jungle serial produced by Republic Pictures. Based loosely on the famous novel Jungle Girl by Edgar Rice Burroughs, this cliffhanger is arguably the best jungle series Republic ever produced. From chapter to chapter, the hunt for hidden African diamonds prompts the beautiful Nyoka (Frances Gifford) and hero Jack Stanton (Tom Neal) to rise to the challenges of the wilderness and the always scheming villains. Re-mastered from a newly discovered 35mm master positive print.

15 Chapters, 267 minutes, 1941
